      <h2>Bathroom Installation in Wirral's Victorian and Period Properties</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Wirral's Victorian terraces and period houses present specific bathroom challenges that catch out inexperienced fitters. Our engineers have been working in Wirral's diverse housing stock for decades and know what to expect before we start.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">The Wirral Outrigger Bathroom Problem</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Victorian terraces in Birkenhead, Wallasey, Hoylake and Rock Ferry frequently have bathrooms added in outrigger extensions at the back of the property. These were typically converted from the original outside toilet and washroom, or added as a separate single-storey extension to the rear of the terrace. Bathrooms in outrigger positions have longer waste pipe runs to connect to the soil stack, which can require fall calculations and sometimes air admittance valves. Floor joists in these positions may need assessment for bath support loads, particularly when replacing a shower with a full-size bath. Original cast iron waste pipes in these extensions are frequently corroded and need replacing rather than reusing. An experienced fitter identifies all of this at the free survey and includes it in the fixed-price quote before any work begins. A less experienced fitter discovers it after strip-out and charges extra.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">South Wirral En Suites and G3 Qualification</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Larger detached and semi-detached properties in Heswall, Pensby and Bromborough are increasingly adding en suites to master bedrooms. When the en suite includes a shower at full mains pressure   as most south Wirral homeowners want   the property typically needs an unvented cylinder to deliver mains pressure hot water to multiple bathrooms simultaneously. Our engineers hold G3 qualification for unvented cylinder installation and inspection, which is a legal requirement for this work. We design, install and certify the complete system   new en suite plus unvented cylinder   in a single project. This is the correct approach for a multi-bathroom south Wirral property, and it eliminates the poor pressure problem that the previous cylinder system was causing in the other bathrooms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">New Bathroom Installation in Wirral Period Houses</strong>
          <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Period houses in West Kirby, Hoylake and Heswall often have bathrooms in positions with solid external walls, limited underfloor void access and original features to preserve. Supply pipes in these properties are usually surface-mounted in neat boxing or run under suspended timber floors rather than chased into solid walls. We plan every pipe route at the free survey and present the routing options before work begins. For period Wirral properties where aesthetics matter, we select fixtures that complement the property character   freestanding baths, column basins and traditional chrome fittings are all available at varying price points within the supply and fit service.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


